last_episode_to_air.name: The Roswell UFO Incident
last_episode_to_air.overview: In 1947, an unidentified flying object crashed near Roswell, NM. Was it a spy balloon or an alien encounter? UFO experts unravel the iconic mystery.

name: Unsolved Mysteries
overview: Real cases of perplexing disappearances, shocking murders and paranormal encounters fuel this gripping revival of the iconic documentary series.

seasons.name: Season 3
seasons.overview: A legendary UFO crash, a puzzling double homicide, a chilling supernatural investigation, perplexing cold cases, historic murders and unexplained creature sightings are reexamined by experts and witnesses in this new collection of mysteries.

episodes.name: Mystery on the Rooftop
episodes.overview: After rushing from his home, Rey Rivera disappears. Days later, his car is found — and a strange sight at a historic hotel triggers a baffling mystery.

episodes.name: 13 Minutes
episodes.overview: Patrice Endres abruptly vanishes from the salon she owned within a 13-minute window of time. Exactly 600 days later, her case takes a shocking turn.

episodes.name: House of Terror
episodes.overview: When an aristocrat and his entire family disappear, the authorities unearth something horrifying.

episodes.name: No Ride Home
episodes.overview: Alonzo Brooks vanishes after a party. His body is found a month later. Many believe that his unsolved death is a hate crime.

episodes.name: Berkshires UFO
episodes.overview: Residents of Berkshire County, Massachusetts, recall their baffling, terrifying experiences with a UFO on the night of September 1, 1969.

episodes.name: Missing Witness
episodes.overview: Lena Chapin claims on tape that her mother killed her stepfather. Several years later, she's issued a subpoena to testify in court — then disappears.

episodes.name: Washington Inside Murder
episodes.overview: Police find the body of former White House aide Jack Wheeler in a landfill. Security footage captures strange events in the days leading up to his death.

episodes.name: A Death in Oslo
episodes.overview: After checking in at a luxury hotel with no ID or credit card, a woman dies from a gunshot. Years later, her identity — and her death — remain a mystery.

episodes.name: Death Row Fugitive
episodes.overview: Given a furlough to go Christmas shopping in 1973, a convicted killer escapes. Police have come close to apprehending him but believe he's still at large.

episodes.name: Tsunami Spirits
episodes.overview: A massive earthquake and tsunami devastated Japan in March 2011. Residents share stories of the spirits they encountered in the wake of the disaster.

episodes.name: Lady in the Lake
episodes.overview: On an icy night, police find JoAnn Romain's abandoned car and assume she drowned in a nearby lake by suicide. But her family suspects foul play.

episodes.name: Stolen Kids
episodes.overview: In May and August 1989, two toddlers vanished from the same New York City park. A search turned up nothing — but their families haven't given up hope.

guest_stars.character: Self - National Center for Missing & Exploited Children
guest_stars.name: Robert Lowery

episodes.name: Mystery at Mile Marker 45
episodes.overview: Tiffany Valiante, a promising young athlete, is struck by a train four miles from home. But was her death a suicide or something more sinister?

episodes.name: Something in the Sky
episodes.overview: Over 300 residents of western Michigan report seeing unearthly lights on the night of March 8th, 1994. Decades later, the event remains unexplained.

episodes.name: Body in Bags
episodes.overview: A beloved father is brutally mutilated, but his presumed killer, a woman he knew from high school, escapes without a trace.

episodes.name: Death in a Vegas Motel
episodes.overview: Buffalo Jim Barrier's larger-than-life presence in Las Vegas rankled the mob. Could that explain his untimely death under suspicious circumstances?

episodes.name: Paranormal Rangers
episodes.overview: Bigfoot, orbs, UFOs, poltergeists and skin-walkers. For these Navajo Nation rangers, paranormal activity is just part of the job.

episodes.name: What Happened to Josh?
episodes.overview: Twenty-year old Josh Guimond leaves a college party without a word and is never seen again. Two decades later, his loved ones just want answers.

episodes.name: Body in the Bay
episodes.overview: Patrick Mullins' unmanned boat is found miles from his home. When his body surfaces a week later, authorities are left with more questions than answers.

episodes.name: The Ghost in Apartment 14
episodes.overview: A woman and her young daughter experience hauntings in their new apartment, linking them to the grisly murder of Marliz Spannhake in 1976

episodes.name: Abducted by a Parent
episodes.overview: When a child is kidnapped by their own parent, what recourse does the family have? These two cases explore the unique pain of parental abduction.

episodes.name: Who Was Jack the Ripper?
episodes.overview: London, 1888. The city is gripped by a string of murders, each more gruesome than the last. Experts delve into one of history's most notorious mysteries.

episodes.name: Body in the Basement
episodes.overview: Amanda Antoni's husband finds her body in their basement with blood everywhere. The scene confounds police: Was it foul play — or a tragic accident?

episodes.name: The Severed Head
episodes.overview: After a teen finds an embalmed head in the woods, investigators uncover a possible connection to a black-market organ trade as they try to ID the victim.

episodes.name: Murder, Center Stage
episodes.overview: Sigrid Stevenson's chilling murder on the stage of a locked campus theater still haunts a New Jersey college as new theories about her killer emerge.

episodes.name: The Mothman Revisited
episodes.overview: Amid eerie sightings of a tall, winged humanoid creature with red eyes, paranormal investigators explore the Mothman's seeming link to major disasters.

episodes.name: Park Bench Murders
episodes.overview: Two friends were shot dead at a busy park on a June day, but the killer escaped unseen. Grieving families are on a hunt for clues about the brazen crime.

episodes.name: My Paranormal Partner
episodes.overview: Paranormal researcher Don has an odd co-worker: an entity named Becky. A parapsychologist observes Don and Becky at work and is stunned by his findings.

episodes.name: Mysterious Mutilations
episodes.overview: For decades, a wave of cattle mutilations executed with near-surgical precision has plagued the US. Are extraterrestrials behind these gruesome acts?

episodes.name: The Roswell UFO Incident
episodes.overview: In 1947, an unidentified flying object crashed near Roswell, NM. Was it a spy balloon or an alien encounter? UFO experts unravel the iconic mystery.
